# Production server safety

Never run `php artisan test` on the production server (`medcahealthcare.com`).

Tests use `User::factory()` which creates faker names like "Dr. Jace Goyette MD" with `@example.org` emails. When config is cached, PHPUnit can accidentally target `database/database.sqlite` (live data) instead of an in-memory database.

Use on **local/staging only**:

- `composer test`
- `./bin/safe-test.sh`

If fake users appear in User Management, they are test artifacts — delete them and avoid running tests on production.
